// Key 

// package - File Structure on PCs .( By Convention - A reversed Domain Name - Traverse L to R for specificity)
// import - Reuse existing code.
// class - Add structure to program code(The code is easy to re-use and read)/ Template of code.
// method - Perform a function. A method can internally call another method. Zero or more method parameters may exist.
// variable(VAR) - A placeholder for a value, the value may change. An instance VAR,  a static VAR , a local VAR ,  a parameter and an argument are all distinct variables.
// Access Modifiers - As public, private, default(Package-Level) & protected for classes as well as methods.
// void - To define a return value when there is no value returned by the method.
// Query Methods - Do not alter the state, return a value.
// Command Methods- Do offer a state but do not return a value.
// @Test - Annotation -  A method to test, if used with annotation.
// CamelCase - For variable and method names in JAVA.
// . - Refer to or use a method for an object.(a.in())
// ; - Indicate the end of a statement in JAVA.
// Object- Instant of a class, reserve memory.
// Object Oriented Programming - Heavily inspired from the concepts of real-world.
// Constructor- The method to create an object from class files.
// Car MyMaruti - Name of VAR  - MyMaruti and type of VAR - Car.
// new - Create a new object, dynamic memory allocation. Car MyMaruti = new Car(1,2).
// MyMaruti is VAR name used to refer to the dynamically created object in the memory of type class 'Car'.